[ The 3rd woman ]

569
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:26,050
I confessed my feelings to her

570
00:23:26,050 --> 00:23:27,860
but I never got a response

571
00:23:27,860 --> 00:23:29,060
I guess I'll ask out Yoda then

572
00:23:29,060 --> 00:23:30,450
[ Settles for Yoda ]

573
00:23:32,300 --> 00:23:34,670
Was Yamashita supposed to be this type of guy?

574
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:35,950
I easily get over things

575
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:37,390
Shiraishi

576
00:23:37,550 --> 00:23:39,410
Does Yamashita's behavior sound wrong to you?

577
00:23:39,410 --> 00:23:41,110
100% Yamashita is the bad person here!

578
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:42,540
That sounds right

579
00:23:42,910 --> 00:23:45,230
What would Kazu-senpai do in this situation?

580
00:23:45,230 --> 00:23:46,280
[ Kazu-senpai! ]

581
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:47,380
Painful isn't it

582
00:23:48,220 --> 00:23:49,940
If that were me

583
00:23:50,260 --> 00:23:51,340
that night...

584
00:23:51,810 --> 00:23:52,940
right through the window

585
00:23:53,470 --> 00:24:04,060
[ The window is the only option ]

586
00:24:04,060 --> 00:24:06,660
The award for Best Fantasy

587
00:24:12,580 --> 00:24:13,660
Tsutsui's

588
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:16,160
library scene

589
00:24:16,260 --> 00:24:19,440
[ Director Tsutsui wins the award for Best Fantasy ]

590
00:24:19,580 --> 00:24:21,380
So my favorite part of that one

591
00:24:21,900 --> 00:24:24,660
it was the overall feeling of gentleness

592
00:24:24,660 --> 00:24:28,150
the moments with no dialogue...it was the dramatic pauses

593
00:24:28,150 --> 00:24:29,940
I really felt the emotions from it

594
00:24:29,940 --> 00:24:31,750
it clutched at my heart

595
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:34,020
omedetou gozaimasu

